§ Definition ⦉
¶ ⦊
  ‖ A probability distribution $p: X → [0,1]$ is ❬log-linear❭ (a
    ❬log-linear probability distribution❭) if the function $f: X →
    𝗥$ defined by
    ◇ ⦊
      ‖ f(x) = \log p(x) \quad \text{for all } x ∈ X ⦉
    ⦉
    is a linear function ⦉
⦉

